{"id":6405,"date":"2024-10-13T19:43:58","date_gmt":"2024-10-13T19:43:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/gei.thomsuninfocare.com\/?p=6405"},"modified":"2026-02-05T10:00:02","modified_gmt":"2026-02-05T10:00:02","slug":"dr-namitha-v-g","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.giridhareye.org\/dr-namitha-v-g\/","title":{"rendered":"Dr. Namitha V G"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 fusion-flex-container has-pattern-background has-mask-background nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row fusion-flex-align-items-flex-start fusion-flex-content-wrap\" style=\"max-width:1414.4px;margin-left: calc(-4% \/ 2 );margin-right: calc(-4% \/ 2 );\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-flex-column\" style=\"--awb-padding-top:40px;--awb-padding-bottom:50px;--awb-bg-size:cover;--awb-width-large:100%;--awb-margin-top-large:0px;--awb-spacing-right-large:1.92%;--awb-margin-bottom-large:20px;--awb-spacing-left-large:1.92%;--awb-width-medium:100%;--awb-order-medium:0;--awb-spacing-right-medium:1.92%;--awb-spacing-left-medium:1.92%;--awb-width-small:100%;--awb-order-small:0;--awb-spacing-right-small:1.92%;--awb-spacing-left-small:1.92%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-column-has-shadow fusion-flex-justify-content-flex-start fusion-content-layout-column\"><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-1 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Educational Qualifications<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p>Dr. Namitha V.G. is a distinguished ophthalmologist with extensive qualifications and experience. She completed her Fellowship in Paediatric Ophthalmology and Strabismus at Giridhar Eye Institute (November 2021 &#8211; December 2023). She is a Member of the Royal College of Surgeons, Edinburgh, and holds a Diploma from the National Board in Ophthalmology, which she earned at Dr. Agarwal\u2019s Eye Hospital, Chennai (2015 &#8211; 2018). Dr. Namitha is also a Fellow of the International Council of Ophthalmology (2018) and holds an M.B.B.S. degree from Kerala University (2007 &#8211; 2012).<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-2 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Specialisation<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><p>Dr. Namitha V.G. specializes in Pediatric Ophthalmology and Strabismus. Her expertise includes the diagnosis and management of simple and complex strabismus, childhood refractive errors, amblyopia, and visual rehabilitation for children with disabilities. She is also skilled in myopia control, pediatric cortical visual impairment, neuro-ophthalmology, and the management of adult amblyopia.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-3 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Work Experience<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-3\"><p>She has amassed valuable work experience in the field of ophthalmology. She served as a Fellow in Pediatric Ophthalmology and Strabismus at Giridhar Eye Hospital from 2021 to 2023. Previously, she worked as a Consultant at Dr. Agarwal\u2019s Eye Hospital and Research Center, Bangalore, from September 2018 to December 2019. During her training, she was a DNB Candidate at Dr. Agarwal\u2019s Eye Hospital and Research Center, Chennai, from 2015 to 2018. Earlier in her career, she also served as a Resident Medical Officer at Malabar Medical College, Calicut, Kerala, in 2014.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-4 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Publications<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-4\"><p>1. Carotid cavernous fistula due to contralateral orbital trauma(Oman journal of ophthalmology 2024)<\/p>\n<p>2. Fleeting diplopia and wobbly feet: Miller\u2010Fisher syndrome\u2010presenting as bilateral abducent nerve palsy(Kerala journal of<\/p>\n<p>ophthalmology DEC 2023)<\/p>\n<p>3. Anterior segment optical coherence tomography in a case of intraocular lens opacification(Kerala journal of<\/p>\n<p>Ophthalmology DEC 2023)<\/p>\n<p>4. Lacteocrumenasia ( Kerala journal of ophthalmology April 2022)<\/p>\n<p>5. IOL power calculation changes before and after collagen crosslinking in keratoconus patients(Indian journal of<\/p>\n<p>ophthalmology 2022)<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-5 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Research Papers And Posters Presented<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-5\"><p>1. Case presentation on Duanes retraction syndrome with dissociated vertical deviation( POSN 2023)<\/p>\n<p>2. Case presentation on Nut Carcinoma(COC 2023)<\/p>\n<p>3. Case presentation on Miller fischer syndrome(neurophthal conclave-coc2023)<\/p>\n<p>4. Physical poster presentation on Tale of an opacified IOL ,a rare postoperative enigma (AIOS-2023)<\/p>\n<p>5. Free paper on Astigmatism correction following femtosecond laser assisted cataract surgery combined with astigmatic<\/p>\n<p>keratotomy(KSOS -2022)<\/p>\n<p>6. Free paper on IOL power calculation changes before and after collagen crosslinking in keratoconus patients (AIOS-2018)<\/p>\n<p>7. Free paper on myopic strabismus fixus \/cfeom a diagnostic dilemma-a case report (AIOS-2018)<\/p>\n<p>8. E-poster on inferior rectus muscle cysticercosis masquerading as mono-ocular elevation deficit-a case report (AIOS- 2018)<\/p>\n<p>9. E-poster on visual outcomes following primary vitrectomy in post operative endophthalmitis &#8211; a case study (AIOS-2018)<\/p>\n<p>10. E-poster on inferior rectus muscle cysticercosis masquerading as mono-ocular elevation deficit-a case report (TNOA- 2017)<\/p>\n<p>11. E-poster on bilateral congenital fibrosis of extraocular muscles with high myopia-a case report (TNOA- 2016)<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-6 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Conferences Attended<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-6\"><p>1. Myopia Conclave by Giridhar Eye Institute, Kochi 2023<\/p>\n<p>2. 5th Grandrounds in Paediatric Ophthalmology and Strabismus Network, Vadodara 2023<\/p>\n<p>3. Neurophthamology conclave by Cochin Ophthalmic Society, Kochi 2023<\/p>\n<p>4. Annual Conference of the All India Ophthalmological Society 2023<\/p>\n<p>5. Kerala Society of Ophthalmic Surgeons (DRISHTI 2022) 2022<\/p>\n<p>6. Annual Conference of the All India Ophthalmological Society2018Indian intraocular implant &amp; Refractive Surgery Convention Scientific Programme 2017<\/p>\n<p>7. Annual Conference Tamil Nadu Ophthalmic Association-Erode 2017<\/p>\n<p>8. Indian intraocular implant &amp; Refractive Surgery Convention Scientific Programme 2016<\/p>\n<p>9. RETICON 2016 Dr Agarwal\u2019s Eye Hospital Chennai 2016<\/p>\n<p>10. Annual Conference Tamil Nadu Ophthalmic Association-Vellore 2016<\/p>\n<p>11. Update on Neuro Ophthalmology at Aravind Eye Hospital Coimbatore 2016<\/p>\n<p>12. RETICON 2015, Chennai 2015 13. Indian intraocular implant &amp; Refractive Surgery Convention Scientific Programme 2015<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-2 fusion-flex-container nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling fusion-animated\" style=\"--awb-background-position:right center;--awb-border-sizes-top:0px;--awb-border-sizes-bottom:0px;--awb-border-sizes-left:0px;--awb-border-sizes-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-padding-top:0px;--awb-padding-right:30px;--awb-padding-bottom:65px;--awb-padding-left:30px;--awb-padding-top-small:125.863px;--awb-margin-top:0px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;--awb-margin-bottom-medium:145px;--awb-background-image:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(1,176,141,0.4) 0%,rgba(1,176,141,0.47) 100%);--awb-background-size:cover;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" data-animationType=\"fadeIn\" data-animationDuration=\"0.8\" data-animationOffset=\"top-into-view\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row fusion-flex-align-items-center fusion-flex-content-wrap\" style=\"max-width:1414.4px;margin-left: calc(-4% \/ 2 );margin-right: calc(-4% \/ 2 );\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-1 fusion-flex-column\" style=\"--awb-padding-top:50px;--awb-padding-right:60px;--awb-padding-bottom:50px;--awb-padding-left:60px;--awb-padding-top-small:50px;--awb-padding-right-small:30px;--awb-padding-bottom-small:50px;--awb-padding-left-small:30px;--awb-bg-color:var(--awb-color1);--awb-bg-color-hover:var(--awb-color1);--awb-bg-size:cover;--awb-width-large:52%;--awb-margin-top-large:0px;--awb-spacing-right-large:16.615384615385%;--awb-margin-bottom-large:-65px;--awb-spacing-left-large:5.5384615384615%;--awb-width-medium:66.666666666667%;--awb-order-medium:0;--awb-spacing-ri